### Ultra-Minimal (Dev + Prod Shared VPC - Selected Approach)

**This is the chosen architecture for initial deployment.**

Running dev and prod in same VPC with shared infrastructure, but **separate RDS instances for safety**:

| Component | Monthly Cost |
|-----------|-------------|
| EC2 t4g.micro (1 instance - shared) | $7 |
| **RDS db.t4g.micro (dev) - single AZ** | **$15** |
| **RDS db.t4g.micro (prod) - single AZ** | **$15** |
| NAT Instance (t4g.nano) | $3 |
| ALB | $22 |
| ECR | $3 |
| Route 53 | $1 |
| CloudWatch (minimal) | $10 |
| SES + SNS + SQS | $25 |
| RDS Backups (both instances) | $6 |
| **Total Shared** | **~$107/month** |

**Why separate RDS instances even in shared VPC:**
* ✅ **Critical safety**: Dev schema changes cannot break prod
* ✅ **Performance isolation**: Dev queries don't slow down prod
* ✅ **Restore confidence**: Can restore prod independently
* ✅ **Cost justified**: $15/month insurance against data loss

**Recommended Starting Point: ~$107/month**

**Cost Reduction Tips:**
* Use **t4g (ARM-based) instances** (20-40% cheaper than t3/t3a)
* Use **NAT Instance** instead of NAT Gateway (saves ~$30/month)
* Use **7-day log retention** instead of 30+ days
* Leverage **free tiers**: SES (62k emails/month from EC2), SQS (1M requests/month), CloudTrail (90-day history)
* Monitor costs with **AWS Budgets** (free) - set alert at $120/month

